Robert E. Sanchez - Ryder System, Inc.

Well, we price our vehicles really based on our medium-term notes, which is really how we fund, how we fund the five-year notes, so that's how we fund the assets. So the way that our pricing works is as interest rates change, we immediately make the change in our pricing model, and the next vehicle that we buy is going to be bought with the – and we price is going to be priced with the higher interest rate.
John R. Cummings - Copeland Capital Management LLC
