SG&A expenses in the second quarter of 2017 and the first half of 2017 decreased
3% and 2% respectively, due to lower compensation-related expenses and favorable
impacts from foreign exchange, partially offset by higher information technology
costs and professional fees. Foreign exchange reduced the growth in SG&A
expenses by 100 basis points. SG&A expenses as a percentage of total revenue
decreased to 11% in both periods.

